# Influencer Signal Rules

Signals from tracked strategy videos (Somesh / Kay Capitals, etc.) are identified by `signal.strategy_video_id != null` and stored in `isInfluencerSignal`.

## These checks are ALREADY SKIPPED for influencer signals — never re-add them:

- ✅ FA validation (`requiresFaValidation = false` when `isInfluencerSignal`)
- ✅ Volume gate (≥1.3x intraday volume)
- ✅ SPY alignment gate
- ✅ Pre-trade risk checks: drawdown protection, allocation cap, sector exposure, earnings blackout (`!isInfluencerSignal` guard on `runPreTradeChecks`)
- ✅ Kelly/drawdown multipliers on position sizing (flat dollar amount used directly)

## These checks still apply — do NOT remove them:

- ❌ Entry trigger not reached (price must hit Somesh's level before executing)
- ❌ Duplicate active trade (same ticker/direction/video already open)
- ❌ Strategy marked X (consecutive losses threshold)

## The reason

Drawdown/allocation/sector checks exist to protect against our own AI-generated (scanner) trades going bad. Influencer signals come from a human expert with their own risk management — our system should not second-guess them. When the portfolio is in critical drawdown, blocking Somesh's signals just means we miss his recovery plays.

## If you ever see `runPreTradeChecks` being called for influencer signals, that is a bug — the guard must be:

```typescript
if (!skipConfirmationGates && !isInfluencerSignal && !(await runPreTradeChecks(...))) {
```
